This Terms of Use ("Agreement") describes conditions under which the International Confederation of Authors and Composers ("CISAC"), as the ISWC International Agency, allows the public to access and use the ISWC-Network ("ISWC-Net"), whether accessed via computer, mobile device or other technology.

Introduction to ISWC
The International Standard Musical Work Code ("ISWC") is a unique, permanent and internationally recognized reference number for the identification of musical works. The ISWC standard has been approved by the International Organization for Standardization ("ISO"), and is currently assigned to by rights management organisations through ISWC registration agencies during the process of registering the musical works with rights management organizations.
Introduction to ISWC-Net
The ISWC-Net facilitates the identification of works and their allocated ISWCs. It contains certain metadata (e.g., title, songwriter(s) and/or composer(s)) relating to works that have been, or are in the process of being, registered with rights management organisations.
The publication of works in the ISWC-Net does not mean that the work is public domain and/or free of any rights. Additionally, the fact that a work does not appear in the ISWC-Net does not mean that the work is in the public domain and/or free of any rights.
Due to complexities in the work registration process, in a limited number of cases, more than one ISWC may have been issued for the same musical work. The ISWC-Net will display the ISWC that should be used (called the Preferred ISWC). Should another ISWC exists for the same work, this ISWC is called "Archived ISWC", which is searchable, but is displayed in the work detail page.

You agree that you will only run manual queries through the ISWC-Net, and will not develop or run scripts or any other tools to generate queries or capture and/or download and store the results automatically. The foregoing prohibition includes, but is not limited to, the practice of embedding the ISWC-Net (or parts thereof) in "frames" or other pages offered from other sites, and "mirroring" content from the ISWC-Net on a server other than that operated by CISAC or its service provider.
